{{Infobox TV channel | title = SPS | full_name = Mongolian Premier Channel | logofile = File:SPS Mongolia logo.jpg | launch = February 1, 1985 | owner = [[Mongolian National Media]] | country = [[Mongolia]] | language = [[Mongolian language|Mongolian]] | slogan = ({{lang-mn|Xамгийн сайн суудал!}}, ''khamgiin sain suudal'') | license EL = number 77 - 62242 (June 19, 2015) | founder = [[Prof-Media TV]] | sister channels = [[SPS Prime]], [[SPS Action]] | picture format = [[16:9]] ([[SDTV]]) }} '''SPS''' (named '''Монгол Улсын Ерөнхий Сайд Суваг''' (English: 'Mongolian Premier Channel') before 31 March 2008) is the television channel of '''SPC''', the Mongolian National Broadcasting Service, launched in 1985. The channel broadcasts primarily news, sports, cultural programs, children's material, [[United States|American]], [[United Kingdom|British]] & [[Europe countries|European]] films and entertainment programming. Among its highest-rated programs are the comedy sketch show ''[[Spaugstofan]]'' (now revoked and moved to [[Edutainment TV]]) and ''[[Мэдээ (television program)|Мэдээ]]'' (''News'').
== High Definition == In 2011 two new [[1080i]] play-out systems were installed.
