'''Step into Dance''' is an inclusive dance programme for secondary schools in London and Essex.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/teacher-network/teacher-blog/2012/jul/03/school-dance-training|title=Harness the positive power of dance|first=Sue|last=Goodman|date=3 July 2012|publisher=|via=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.londonfestivalofeducation.com/step-into-dance|title=London Festival of Education 2015 - Step into Dance|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sadlerswells.com/whats-on/2016/jack-petchey-foundation-and-royal-academy-of-dance-step-live-2016/|title=Jack Petchey Foundation & Royal Academy of Dance - Step Live! 2016 - Sadler's Wells Theatre|publisher=}}</ref> The programme is run by the [[Royal Academy of Dance]] and funded by the Jack Petchey Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/education/best-of-london-s-trailblazing-state-schools-honoured-at-our-awards-a3128141.html|title=Best of London's ‘trail-blazing’ state schools honoured at our awards|date=2 December 2015|publisher=}}</ref> The programme began in 2007 after [[Jack Petchey]] approached the RAD with an idea to set up an extra-curricular dance programme for young people in London.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disabilityartsonline.org.uk/step-into-dance-inclusive-dance-programme|title=News: Step into Dance: Inclusive dance practice... unlocking creativity and freeing inhibitions - disability arts online|publisher=}}</ref> Initially targeting particular boroughs in London, Step into Dance launched with a pilot of 30 schools. In 2008 Sue Goodman joined as Artistic Director, bringing a focus on performance and high quality choreography. Since then the programme has grown year by year, with 200 schools participating in 2015/16.<ref>http://www.croydonguardian.co.uk/news/10360654.Putney_set_for_dance_extravanza/extravanza/</ref> The programme is one of the Jack Petchey Foundation's flagship projects, alongside several other major initiatives for young people that the organisation fund, including The Speak Out Challenge and The Achievement Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jackpetcheyfoundation.org.uk/step-into-dance|title=Jack Petchey Foundation – Step into Dance|publisher=}}</ref> As of July 2016 the Foundation had donated over 3 million pounds to the programme and over 30 thousand students have participated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://philanthropy.coutts.com/en/reports/2015/united-kingdom/case-studies/jack-petchey.html|title=JACK PETCHEY - UK Case Studies - Coutts Million Dollar Donor Report|publisher=}}</ref> In March 2014, Step into Dance launched its Young Ambassador Scheme.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guardian-series.co.uk/news/13333161.Pupil_becomes_borough_s_first_dance_ambassador/|title=Pupil becomes borough's first dance ambassador|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://londondance.com/youth-dance/articles/step-into-dance-youth-ambassadors-get-cracking-wit/|title=Step Into Dance Youth Ambassadors get cracking with Parliamentary letter-writing campaign - LondonDance|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.danceuk.org/news/article/step-dance-launches-young-ambassadors-scheme/|title=Step into Dance launches Young Ambassadors scheme — News — Dance UK|publisher=}}</ref>
